WEBVTT

00:12:28.506 --> 00:12:30.664
And they have a lot to lose
by taking a risk,

00:12:30.688 --> 00:12:33.751
and they're also, of course,
often selected to move up that way,

00:12:33.775 --> 00:12:37.140
by their ability to conform
and enforce routines and norms and rules.

00:12:37.531 --> 00:12:41.245
Do you have any thoughts on how to open
the minds of middle managers?

00:12:41.952 --> 00:12:44.715
SD: I mean ... um ... no.

00:12:46.436 --> 00:12:48.037
AG: (Laughs) That's not helpful.

00:12:48.061 --> 00:12:49.214
SD: But I mean --

00:12:49.238 --> 00:12:51.204
AG: Ladies and gentlemen, Stephen Dubner.

00:12:51.228 --> 00:12:54.839
SD: But the knee-jerk response
would be incentives,

00:12:54.863 --> 00:12:57.640
because economics believes in incentives.

00:12:57.664 --> 00:13:00.291
The problem is,